{
  "text": "Indirana chiravasi can be distinguished from I. brachytarsus in having few longitudinal folds on dorsal side (vs. numerous longitudinal folds on dorsal side), thin, shovel-shaped inner metatarsal tubercle (vs. long and stout inner metatarsal tubercle) moderate webbing (vs. extensive webbing, webbing formula, I1-2II1-21/2III1-3IV3-1V) and having broader head . Furthermore, if the identification of I. brachytarsus by [CITATION_1] is correct then the two species are also genetically quite distinct (Fig. 3) . Raw genetic distance between I. chiravasi sp. nov. and I. brachytarsus (as identified by [CITATION_2] ) is 11.6% for 16S gene and 8. 0-8.3 % for all the genes together.",
  "correct_citation": {
